<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="246" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,639,359,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,280,678,699]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
See diagnosis under 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[501,638,678,699]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorynota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monoceros">
<emphasis box="[501,638,678,699]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. monoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<tableCitation box="[194,268,704,725]" captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="5.[175,223,1489,1508]" captionText="Table 2. Diagnostic characters distinguishing Dorynota monoceros, Dorynota pugnax, and Dorynota borowieci." pageId="15" pageNumber="246">Table 2</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="246" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,639,359,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,275,731,752]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boheman &amp; Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus secundus. Ex Officina Norstedtiana &amp; Holmiae &amp; Sweden" box="[288,459,731,752]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" refId="ref16598" refString="Boheman, C. H. 1854. Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus secundus. Ex Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, Sweden." type="book" year="1854">Boheman (1854)</bibRefCitation>
did not state the precise number of specimens. However, he mentioned ‘Mus. Dom. Chevrolat’ as the depository and gave single length and width measurements. In such cases, Boheman always had a single specimen, and because there is only a single specimen in the Chevrolat collection, we consider it the 
<typeStatus box="[271,360,917,938]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">holotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,639,359,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">
The species was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[535,638,943,964]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorynota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis box="[535,638,943,964]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. nodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Spaeth" box="[181,315,970,991]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" pagination="65 - 76" refId="ref17858" refString="Spaeth, F. 1923. Ueber Batonota Hope. (Col. Cassid.). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung 40 (1 - 4): 65 - 76." type="journal article" year="1923">Spaeth (1923)</bibRefCitation>
based on the primary description. However, examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[456,498,996,1017]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">type</typeStatus>
revealed that this species is actually morphologically close to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[151,284,1050,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorynota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monoceros">
<emphasis box="[151,284,1050,1071]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. monoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and not to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Boheman" baseAuthorityYear="1854" box="[393,492,1050,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorynota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodosa">
<emphasis box="[393,492,1050,1071]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. nodosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The latter distinctly differs in that it has a very short dorsal spine, which is barely longer than the width of its base, and the elytra are strongly emarginate and more protruding behind the humeral angles. Therefore, we restore 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" box="[436,537,1183,1204]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Batonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugnax">
<emphasis box="[436,537,1183,1204]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. pugnax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to species status. It can be separated from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[495,638,1209,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorynota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monoceros">
<emphasis box="[495,638,1209,1230]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. monoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its shorter elytral spine, less dense and finer punctation on the elytra, and the elytra with mostly distinct intervals, while 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Germar" baseAuthorityYear="1824" box="[498,637,1289,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Dorynota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="monoceros">
<emphasis box="[498,637,1289,1310]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. monoceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has very coarse and dense elytral punctation with very narrow intervals and punctures nearly touching each other.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,639,359,1575]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">
The species is also probably found in 
<collectingCountry box="[540,637,1395,1416]" name="Venezuela" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
as the specimen reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Boheman &amp; Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus quartus &amp; Supplementum &amp; Ex Officina Norstedtiana &amp; Holmie &amp; Sweden" box="[462,637,1421,1442]" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" refId="ref16656" refString="Boheman, C. H. 1862. Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus quartus (Supplementum). Ex Officina Norstedtiana, Holmie, Sweden." type="book" year="1862">Boheman (1862)</bibRefCitation>
under 
<taxonomicName box="[219,349,1448,1469]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Batonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiator">
<emphasis box="[219,349,1448,1469]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. gladiator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and cited here most likely belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" box="[260,361,1475,1496]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Batonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="246" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pugnax">
<emphasis box="[260,361,1475,1496]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="246">D. pugnax</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
